snippet.description:

🔈🎧 Out Today - Altered Forms & Cybergrass - You Know It
Out next in Iono Music is the single called "You Know It" by Altered Forms & Cybergrass featuring Murus. Step into a new dimension of psytrance with "You Know It," the latest collaborative track from Altered Forms and Cybergrass, featuring Murus, soon to be released on Iono Music. This track is a fusion of innovation and tradition, creating a sonic experience that captivates and energizes. Together, they have crafted a track that transcends the typical boundaries of psytrance, incorporating elements of progressive and vocal trance to create a mesmerizing blend of music that speaks directly to the soul.

★★★ Promote and Spread Psychedelic Trance Worldwide! ★★★
This channel was opened in March 2013 with the purpose of promoting Psy-Trance artists & spreading their awe-inspiring music worldwide! 
It features all the latest from your favorite artists and projects, and also revive classic tracks and albums from the past, every once in a while. 
I founded this channel for my love for Psytrance - a genre I have walked hand in hand with since before it was even created. From the era of the Dark '80s to Techno, Goa Trance & to today's style. Partying since 1994, visited Goa in 1996 - its best time, and through all the years always involved in what's out & what's new. 
I live & breathe Psytrance & dedicate this channel to those who share the same love!

Amelie Lens - Hypnotized EP [SNDST063]

1: Amelie Lens - Hypnotized
2: Amelie Lens - Access
3: Amelie Lens - Hypnotized (Joyhauser Remix)

One and a half years since her last outing on Second State, Amelie Lens returns to the label with her highly anticipated new 3-tracker, ‘Hypnotized EP‘. Following up to the much acclaimed ‘Basiel EP’ issued in 2018 through her own imprint, Lenske, Amelie steps up right in time for the much busy festival season ahead with a pair of razor-sharp peaktime weapons, plus a nasty gabber-inflected remix from rising Belgian duo Joyhauser. With upcoming dates including performances at Sónar, Movement, Awakenings, Exit, Kappa Future and Sonus, needless to say these are bound to get dance floors on fire this summer.

Having triggered a massive response from the audience during her sets over the last year, the title track ’Hypnotized‘ breaks the ice on a fiercely pounding note. Flexing out the heavy kick artillery, brooding chord stabs and cascading snares while Amelie’s delayed vox hooks steadily sink us into a whelming state of trance. Reaching for the most remote recesses of the dancers’ minds, ‘Access’ revs up the engine a notch further with its psychoactive synthwaves, furling and swirling across full bars of louder than loud 909 thump. Adding their euphoric spin to the lead cut, ‘Hypnotized’, Joyhauser seal the deal with an all-out ravey anthem of a rework, custom-built for epic, warehouse-sized maneuvers and iron-pumping mid-set apexes. Shockwaves are coming.

Written and produced by Amelie Lens.

Sinfol readies a two-part release on his Anagram Label featuring Anetha, Elad Magdasi, Octual and more. Tying things together, Front Left Records' Elad Magdasi's 'Two Floors' closes off the release in an epic manner with thudding kicks and otherworldly melodies.

snippet.title: Battle Of The Future Buddhas - Strange Fantasy
snippet.description:
Subscribe: https://youtube.com/SuntripRecords?sub_confirmation=1
Buy: https://suntriprecords.bandcamp.com/album/cause-principle-and-one-eternal

Battle of the Future Buddhas - Cause, Principle and One Eternal, released on 06. Dec 2024 by Suntrip Records - SUNCD81

With this double album Battle of the Future Buddhas both continue the softer old school journey with melodic and cool yet trippy music on one side, and takes a few steps back to Twin Sharkfins territory and goes back to the own roots with faster, darker and relentlessly psychedelic dance stormers. We are literally going from the Edge of the Void, to the Apex and To Hell and it’s really a Strange Fantasy all in all. 

Each CD has it’s distinct own journey, the first slowly and carefully building up to a peak and the other one just going on the Attack right away. It is not really morning and night music, as there is melancholia and some darkness, but always melodic, so it’s more a dawn and a dusk side. But there is a great range of different tracks, from the melodic and powerfully uplifting Magneto to the dark almost industrial even death metal like landscape of Evermore. 

The production on the dawn side is kind of low and careful and it is mixed low, with lots of room for melodies to evolve on their own, undisturbed by hectic or chaotic sounds, or a too powerful kick or bass. All basslines are funky and unique by the way, usually with delays making them float and groove around. There are some faster and more energetic pieces aimed for the dance floor as well.

The dusk side is mixed loud, with sounds trying to be heard over the general mayhem and conquering their own frequency. Tracks are generally faster, more intense and definitely very psychedelic, yet melodic. Night music can for sure have melodies and every track has its own interpretation of melodies. Overall this CD is aimed at the most intense peaks on the dance floor, but there are no machine gun basslines.*

No compression is used in the production, except to master the tracks. But not as a tool to get the kick and the bass to give more oomph. This allows for the rest of the sounds, the melodies, to dominate and tell a story, instead of being yet another empty sound quality focused production. Sound quality might mean chosing the right sound to tell a story, not just having perfectly spectralized waves and frequencies. 

As usual in the 2000s it’s David who is making the most of the productions, but Johan has co-created Centurion and has provided feedback and added rhythms and other sounds on Broken Bass and Flumerider as well.

Suntrip Records is an old-style Goa-Trance label launched in 2004, releasing melodic, acidic, and darker Goa-Trance on CD, vinyl, and of course digital for two decades now. Many big names like Astral Projection, Filteria, Shakta, Mindsphere, Dimension 5, Triquetra, Tim Schuldt, and Goasia have released their albums on Suntrip. Their goal was, and still is, to keep this magical music alive for new generations to come so they can dance and experience what Goa-Trance is all about.

Classic Goa Trax is a sublabel of Suntrip Records founded in 2019, focusing on digital re-releases of classical Goa albums & never-before-released 90s Goa-Trance only. Because so many of the releases of the 90s are unavailable or sold second-hand at crazy prices, we want to give a platform to access this music for the new digital generation. Goa lovers can get some of the most wanted releases at the Bandcamp of Classic Goa Trax for a reasonable price while supporting both the label and the artists.

So, if you like the music we release, please go to our Bandcamp to support us and great Goa musicians while adding to your collection and keeping the scene and vibe alive.

3. Resonance


In the midst of a meteoric rise and a riding high of her recent release on Pig & Dan’s Elevate imprint, Amelie Lens returns home to Second State with an absolutely stellar three tracker delivering her signature sound of sultry vocals, cryptic atmospheres and massive drums. The ‘Contradiction’ EP kicks off with the title track of the same name with an enormous kick drum as fragments of Amelie’s lush vocals introduce a fever inducing acid line culminating in a rugged yet profoundly energetic tune, proving that less is truly more. ‘Drift’ follows suit and once again proves that Amelie’s minimalist approach has massive results. By utilizing a few powerful elements, ‘Drift’ dives into the heavy ethereal creating the perfect balance between tension and serenity. Wrapping up the release Lens delivers the most psychedelic cut of the EP with ‘Resonance’. Another masterpiece in the minimal approach, Amelie utilizes a simple shimmering synth as the vehicle in which to traverse a dark world of intense percussive sonics. Get ready to take a journey. Amelie Lens is back.
